The CBD tea market can be segmented based on various factors, one of which is the types of tea available in the market. The market offers both organic and conventional options to cater to the preferences of different consumer segments. Organic CBD tea is witnessing substantial demand due to the increasing consumer preference for natural and organic products. Another key segmentation factor is the flavors offered in CBD tea products. Popular flavors include chamomile, peppermint, matcha, and various other blends that provide unique taste experiences to consumers. Additionally, the distribution channels play a crucial role in reaching out to target audiences. CBD tea products are distributed through online retail platforms as well as brick and mortar stores, providing convenient access to consumers.

**Market Players**

